title: Age distribution in the Netherlands 2008 to 2018
summary: You are viewing a chart of multi-line type with 3 lines denoting Ages 0-14, Ages 15-64, and Ages 65+. The y axis indicates the Share of population and the x axis indicates Year.
Overall Ages 65+ is gradually increasing, Ages 0-14, and Ages 15-64 are roughly constant,  throughout the Year
The lines ordered according to average values of Share of population in descending order is: 1. Ages 15-64, 2. Ages 0-14, and lastly, 3. Ages 65+.
Overall across the Year, Ages 15-64 mostly maintained the highest Share of population when compared to others with a mean value of 66.03, and it peaked at 2008.
After Ages 15-64, Ages 0-14 overall has the second highest values , with a mean value of 17.0, peaking at 2008.
Ages 65+ mostly had the least Share of population with a mean value of 16.93, which peaked at 2018 with a value of 19.2.
